<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="380">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181845" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole boliviana Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole boliviana Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviana">Pheidole boliviana</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="380">Types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="380">Etymology Named after country of origin of the type series.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="380">
Diagnosis Medium-sized brown member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group, whose major and minor have exceptionally long, abundant, erect to suberect hairs over most of the body, foveolate and opaque mesosoma and petiole, and small, nearly oval postpetiolar node only slightly wider than the petiolar node.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="380">Major: promesonotum with convexities in dorsal-oblique view; petiolar node in rear view strongly convex; carinulae on the midline dorsum of the head reach the occiput.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="380">Minor: humerus angulate in dorsal-oblique view; dorsal surface of head mostly foveolate and opaque.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="380">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181837" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole amabilis Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole amabilis Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">amabilis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181899" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole melastomae Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole melastomae Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melastomae">melastomae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181905" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole mixteca Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole mixteca Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixteca">mixteca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181940" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole scitula Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole scitula Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scitula">scitula</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34052" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole terresi Wheeler &amp; Mann" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole terresi Wheeler &amp; Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terresi">terresi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34074" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tysoni Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tysoni Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="380" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tysoni">tysoni</taxonomicName>
, differing in the combination of traits cited above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="380">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.86, HL 0.90, SL 0.46, EL 0.14, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="380">Paratype minor: HW 0.50, HL 0.54, SL 0.44, EL 0.10, PW 0.34.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="380">Color Major: head, mesosoma, waist, gaster, and antennae dark brown; legs brownish yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="380">Minor: dorsa of head and mesosoma medium brown; rest of body medium brown to brownish yellow; appendages brownish yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="380">Range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
